Create a Directional Light game object [A].\
\
Note its transform component [B] by default has the light shining down 50 degrees at some heading. For a directional light, position is irrelevant (because it's assumed to be infinitely far away, approximating a distant light source such as the sun). It's typical to place it at X=0 and Z=0, but higher up such as Y=100, just to keep it out of the way.\
\
Note its light component [C]. Here you can set the light's intensity and also colour it. Another interesting setting is shadows: change it to Soft Shadows and reduce the shadow strength to 0.5; notice the effect on the shadows cast by the trees.\
\
Typically one would match a directional light's rotation, colour, and intensity to the skybox.\
\
