Note its transform component. For a point light, rotation is irrelevant (because it's assumed to be omnidirectional, approximating a light source like a bare bulb). Place it near the origin but a few meters off the ground (e.g. Y=10).\
\
Note its light component [D]. Here you can set the light's intensity and also colour it (e.g. red). Another interesting setting is range: change it to 50 and note how it has a similar (but not the same) effect as intensity. Unfortunately, shadows are not supported on point lights with Unity Free.\
